& [ExecutionGateDecisionWriterDesign] is the design contract for explicitly persisting execution gate decisions
  @ [source_design] coordination/worker_execution_gate_design.sop
  @ [preview_design] coordination/execution_gate_preview_cli_design.sop
  @ [record_model] src/negotiated_agent/execution_gate.py
  @ [manager_job_notice] coordination/manager_job_notice.sop
  @ [created_at] 2026-05-29T20:12:00Z

  + [design_status] is ready_for_implementation_slice
  + [authority_boundary] is gate_decision_write_not_worker_execution
  + [primary_goal] is persist an ExecutionGateDecision generated from existing Manager authorization Shaliach clearance lease and frontier evidence
  + [non_goal] is creating ManagerAuthorizationRecord
  + [non_goal] is creating ShaliachExecutionClearance
  + [non_goal] is claiming mailbox messages or advancing read cursors
  + [non_goal] is executing worker implementation work
  + [non_goal] is mutating the active Manager frontier or target workspace

& [DecisionWriterInputs] is what the writer command must accept
  + [required_arg] is project_root
  + [required_arg] is worker_uuid
  + [required_arg] is manager_authorization_ref
  + [required_arg] is shaliach_clearance_ref
  + [required_arg] is lease_ref
  + [required_arg] is current_frontier or active conversation lookup
  + [optional_arg] is gate_id
  + [optional_arg] is output_dir defaulting to coordination/workers/<worker_uuid>/execution_gates
  + [authority_boundary] is writer_inputs_existing_evidence_only
  = must: reject missing or malformed required refs
  = must: preserve input refs exactly as supplied in the written decision

& [DecisionWriterOutput] is the only allowed mutation
  + [artifact_name] is coordination/workers/<worker_uuid>/execution_gates/<gate_id>.sop
  + [artifact_body] is ExecutionGateDecision.to_sop()
  + [stdout_summary] is written artifact path plus gate_status
  + [exit_code_zero] is decision artifact written successfully, even when gate_status is blocked
  + [exit_code_nonzero] is malformed input, missing input file, output containment failure, or existing output collision
  + [authority_boundary] is persisted_decision_not_completion_approval
  = must: create the execution_gates directory when absent
  = must: refuse to overwrite an existing gate artifact unless a future explicit replacement protocol is designed
  = must: keep manager authorization, Shaliach clearance, lease, claims, read cursors, active conversation, worker cycles, and target workspace files unchanged
  = must: include execution_gate_decision_not_completion_approval in the written artifact

& [BlockedDecisionHandling] is the evidence behavior when execution is not allowed
  + [blocked_status] is blocked_by_manager, blocked_by_shaliach, stale_frontier, or lease_invalid
  + [write_behavior] is still write the blocked ExecutionGateDecision for review
  + [follow_up] is a later worker cycle command may record paused_by_manager, paused_by_shaliach, stale_frontier, or failed_preflight using this gate ref
  + [authority_boundary] is blocked_gate_record_not_failure_recovery
  = must: not repair inputs automatically
  = must: not request new Manager authorization automatically
  = must: not produce a WorkerCycleRecord inside the gate writer

& [ProofExpectations] is the minimum implementation proof for this design
  + [test_case] is writes allowed proof-only decision to the default worker execution_gates directory
  + [test_case] is writes blocked decision and exits zero without executing work
  + [test_case] is rejects output path outside coordination worker gate directory
  + [test_case] is refuses to overwrite an existing gate artifact
  + [test_case] is leaves claim, cursor, cycle, authorization, clearance, and lease refs unchanged

& [ImplementationOrder] is the safe next split
  + [slice_1] is add pure write_execution_gate_decision helper around the existing evaluator
  + [slice_2] is add explicit CLI write mode and PowerShell wrapper
  + [slice_3] is add tests proving only the gate artifact is written
  + [slice_4] is document operator use after behavior is stable
